  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "NumPyro provides efficient implementations of various MCMC algorithms, including the affine-invariant en-semble sampler implemented in emcee and NUTS.",
    "In our tests, NUTS implemented in NumPyro achieves up to a tenfold speed increase over emcee in generating 5000 effective posterior samples (n eff), when applied to the same set of two-band light curves and using identical prior distributions for EzTaoX parameters.",
    "Unbiased recovery of τ DRW depends on the light-curve cadence, baseline (i.e., the total duration of observations), and adopted priors.",
    "As shown by Kozłowski (2017) and later studies (e.g., Sánchez-Sáez et al. 2018; Burke et al. 2021; Suberlak et al. 2021; Hu et al. 2024), τ DRW is systematically underestimated when the lightcurve baseline is shorter than ∼10 times the true τ DRW.",
    "Hu et al. (2024) conducted extensive simulations demonstrating that the assumed prior on τ DRW also impact its recovery."
  ],
